text:
Thank you <@UV23JHEJY> and <@UK9BKNBD5>. Maybe I’m missing something here, but both solutions don’t appear to be dynamic and look like they require calling upon a very specific blog ID in order to propagate the posts. Given this is going to being global sidebar to many posts, I need to make this module dynamic.

This is what I have so far for the sidebar module. _(Attached is an image of what I’m attempting to achieve. Sidebar module is in the red box)_
```&lt;!-- Display the tag name of the current post --&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Other {{ tag.name }} FAQs&lt;/h5&gt;

  &lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;!-- Looks for posts that have the same tag as the current post and displays the 5 most recent --&gt;
    {% set related_blog_posts limit=5 %}
    {% for tag_post in blog_recent_tag_posts %}
      &lt;li&gt;
          &lt;!-- Posts the title of related posts --&gt;
          &lt;a href="{{ content.absolute_url }}"&gt;{{ content.name }}&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
    {% endfor %}
  &lt;/ul&gt;

 &lt;!-- Link to Archive of Posts that Match the Current Posts Tag --&gt;
&lt;a href="{{ current_post__tag_url }}"&gt;See More&lt;/a&gt;```
